Boil a #kettle{}.

While it boils, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Trim the @green beans{150%g}, then cut into thirds.

Add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} to a #medium bowl{}. Add the @cornflour{10%g}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss to coat.

== Cooking the Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the diced chicken to the pan. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Noodles and Beans ==

In the meantime, pour the boiled water into a #large saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and green beans to the water. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

== Making the Sauce ==

Once the chicken has cooked, add the garlic and @ginger puree{15%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @water for the sauce{125%ml} and half the lemon zest. Cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, add a squeeze of lemon juice from a lemon wedge to the sauce.

Stir in the cooked noodles, green beans, @honey{30%g} and @butter{10%g}, then mix until well-coated.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== To Serve ==

Share your lemon chicken noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} and any remaining lemon zest.

> Making this kid friendly? Serve the sesame in a little bowl for optional sprinkling.